story*
George gets a new toy, and he doesn't know how to use it. Harold finds George and they try to figure out how to use the toy. They start to throw the toy up in the air and to each other. Harold threw the toy too high and lost sight of it, it fell and broke. 
George is very upset and mad, mad at Harold. "are you okay?" asks Harold. "NO!" says George, "I am mad! I am mad and sad!"
"I'm sorry" says Harold. "Well sorry does not fix my toy" says George. Bob the squirrel is walking by, he notices the new toy that George has.
"Wow!" says Bob. "It's a break-snap toy". "A what?" says George. "A break-snap toy, You break it and put it back together!" says Bob. 
